To solve the given system of linear equations using block matrices, we first write the system in matrix form:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
4 & 2 & 3 \\
2 & 5 & 4 \\
6 & 3 & 2
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
x \\
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
22 \\
35 \\
28
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Now, we partition the coefficient matrix into block matrices:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
A_{11} & A_{12} \\
A_{21} & A_{22}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
X_1 \\
X_2
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
B_1 \\
B_2
\end{bmatrix}
$$

where

$$
A_{11} = \begin{bmatrix}
4
\end{bmatrix},
A_{12} = \begin{bmatrix}
2 & 3
\end{bmatrix},
A_{21} = \begin{bmatrix}
2 \\
6
\end{bmatrix},
A_{22} = \begin{bmatrix}
5 & 4 \\
3 & 2
\end{bmatrix},
X_1 = \begin{bmatrix}
x
\end{bmatrix},
X_2 = \begin{bmatrix}
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix},
B_1 = \begin{bmatrix}
22
\end{bmatrix},
B_2 = \begin{bmatrix}
35 \\
28
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Now we can solve the system using block matrices:

1. Solve $A_{11}X_1 + A_{12}X_2 = B_1$ for $X_1$:

$$
4x + 2y + 3z = 22
$$

2. Solve $A_{21}X_1 + A_{22}X_2 = B_2$ for $X_2$:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
2 \\
6
\end{bmatrix}
x +
\begin{bmatrix}
5 & 4 \\
3 & 2
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
35 \\
28
\end{bmatrix}
$$

3. Substitute the expression for $X_1$ from step 1 into step 2:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
2 \\
6
\end{bmatrix}
\left(\frac{22 - 2y - 3z}{4}\right) +
\begin{bmatrix}
5 & 4 \\
3 & 2
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
35 \\
28
\end{bmatrix}
$$

4. Simplify the system and solve for $X_2$:

$$
\begin{bmatrix}
5 & 4 \\
3 & 2
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
y \\
z
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
35 - \frac{11}{2}y - \frac{9}{2}z \\
28 - 3y - 9z
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Solving this system, we get:

$$
y = 3, \quad z = 2
$$

5. Substitute the values of $y$ and $z$ back into the expression for $x$:

$$
x = \frac{22 - 2(3) - 3(2)}{4} = \frac{10}{4} = \frac{5}{2}
$$

Thus, the solution to the system of linear equations is:

$$
x = \frac{5}{2}, \quad y = 3, \quad z = 2
$$
